<br>
Then there was the sign hanging over Mike (3/7) Company's CP. <br><br>
&quot; YOU'RE A MARINE, OUR JOB IS TO KILL GOOKS, AND KILLING IS GOOD!&quot;<br><br>
Oh, and the one at Battalion Headquarters,<br><br>
&quot;YOU'RE HERE BECAUSE YOU WANT THE REAL THING!&quot;<br><br>
The gooks also got into the act, they made a large sign for us on Christmas eve, send it down the river to us in a hand made basket. <br>
The large banner said Merry Christmas and the note attached was signed by the local communist cadre member of the Liberation Army.<br>
The note mentioned many of us by name and showed they had set a certain bounty upon some of our heads.<br>
Captains were $200.00 Dollars in US Currency, Liuetenants $150, but grunts they would only offer $2.00 apiece for us, That was the ultimate insult, but it showed that they also had a sense of humor. Still have a picture of that sign. 
